explanation: The solution uses a HashMap to count the occurrences of each element in the array. Then, it uses a HashSet to check if any two counts are the same.  This approach has a time complexity of O(n) due to iterating through the array once to count occurrences and once to check for duplicates. The space complexity is O(n) in the worst case, where all elements are unique, as the HashMap and HashSet could store up to n elements.

